headline: Deckers Stock Is Among the Worst Performers in the S&P 500 in 2025. Should Investors Buy the Dip?
summary: Shares of shoe company Deckers Outdoor (NYSE: DECK) are down about 37% in 2025, as of this writing, giving it the third worst performance for a constituent of the S&P 500.  Deckers stock was added to the S&P 500 in March 2024.  By contrast, the S&P 500 is up about 15% during that time, which is an above-average gain for a 52-week span.
